text: Toomsuba Creek is a stream in the U.S. states of Alabama and Mississippi. Toomsuba is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean either (sources vary) "blue pigeon hawk" or "fish hawk". Variant names are "Tonsabah Creek", "Tonsobah Creek", "Tonsubah Creek", "Toomseba Creek", "Toomsebah Creek", and "Toomsooba Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Sumter County, Alabama Category:Bodies of water of Lauderdale County, Mississippi
title: Toomsuba Creek
